# ROVEXO v1.0 Global Preview Policy — Officially Locked

Applies without exception to every user-facing module and future page. Non-visual
work must preview every affected surface. One module means one canonical implementation.

## Mandatory sequence

Build → Implementation → Visual Preview → Responsive Testing → QA Testing →
User-Flow Testing → Product Owner Approval → Freeze → Commit → Push →
Preview Deployment → Production Validation → Production Deployment → Lock.

Never skip, reorder, combine, or infer authorization between stages.

## Required visual evidence

Every module must provide all seven artifacts before approval:
1. iPhone 17 Pro Max preview
2. Samsung Galaxy Ultra preview
3. Desktop preview
4. PWA preview
5. Responsive composite preview
6. Complete user-flow preview
7. Final official preview

Evidence must show the final appearance and behavior: spacing, cards, imagery,
navigation, scrolling, motion/transitions, loading, responsive layouts, and
empty-state behavior (including omission where the approved spec hides empties).
Static specifications, code, contracts, or test output alone are never approval evidence.

Required surfaces include Homepage, Search, Sell, Inbox Hub, Product, Checkout,
Wallet, Account, Settings, Admin, Business tools/profile verification, and every
future UI. “Business” never creates a separate account type or role-switching flow.

## Human approval hard stop

After previews and tests, stop and wait for explicit Product Owner approval.
Before approval, never freeze, commit, push, merge, deploy, production-lock,
release, or start a later release stage. Praise is not approval. Authorization
is stage-specific and never carries forward implicitly.

## Release gates

No preview = no approval. No approval = no Freeze. No Freeze = no Commit.
No Commit = no Push. No Push = no Deploy. No final official visual preview means
the module may never be deployed or locked.
